<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-05T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760p.6111/48: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-05T21:00:00+03:00">October 5,
                                    1939—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 5—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>687. The Soviet-Latvian pact was signed this afternoon. Following a
                            dinner at the Kremlin the Latvian Foreign Minister left this evening by
                            train for Riga. The text of the pact is not yet available but is
                            expected to be released tonight by Tass.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Riga.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>